value.0: I hope you enjoy your time in Highcliff, and stay safe. Goodbye.
Oh. He lives in a manor around Wolfhill Way. If you wanted to visit him, that's southwest of Highcliff. Luxurious, you know? Alhelor's usually here, but he said he was tired.

Oh, I'm sorry. He's a peddler... he's usually here most days, but he said he was tired and went home early. He lives in a manor around Wolfhill Way. If you wanted to visit him, that's southwest of Highcliff.
Maybe you can stop in tomorrow? We sell the best collection of werewolf remedies around. Well, we're the only ones selling stuff like that... but we're the best!
Thank you. I'll tell you where the three of my friends are probably are now. As they are now, you know, werewolves, you'll likely only find them at night.
Bran liked the mysteriousness of Grizzly Lake. I wouldn't be surprised if he's there now. You'll find the body of water to the northeast of Highcliff. As the name suggest, beware of bears.

Geth... he was the one that talked me into doing this... he always dragged me out to the Waterfall Beach, thinking we'd find nymphs and other fey spirits. Maybe he went there. It's located northwest of Highcliff.

Urth didn't really have any particular place he'd be. His family might know. I want to ask them myself, but... I'm too ashamed to speak to them. Perhaps if you speak to them, they may give a clue as to where he may be. They live on a farm on the High Road, north of Highcliff.
Please, return to me and tell me of their fate.

Comment.value:
hostile reaction
about 50% of NPC's can probably end their conversation here
for the purposes of this example, we'll continue

value.0: I... I suppose there's no harm in talking about it, if Alhelor says it's okay. He said that I should try to forget about it... stop thinking about it so much. I don't know. I try. Sometimes I feel kind of normal, and then -

All I can see are those eyes looking out from the cave, and there's that feeling of knowing something is wrong - total fear. Anyway... Karathis was a werewolf hunter, and he came here to hunt the Black Wolf! That's what we call Highcliff's werewolf.
We found wolf tracks and followed them to a cave. Karathis went in while we set up camp. It's just outside of Waterfall Beach, that cave... in the coast northeast of Highcliff.

I... I suppose there's no harm in talking about it, since Alhelor isn't here right now. He said that I should try to forget about it... stop thinking about it so much. I don't know. I try. Sometimes I feel kind of normal, and then -

All I can see are those eyes looking out from the cave, and there's that feeling of knowing something is wrong - total fear. Anyway... Karathis was a werewolf hunter, and he came here to hunt the Black Wolf! That's what we call Highcliff's werewolf.
That's okay. I hope that they are still alive and well, even in their... state. I just wish I was a bit more brave, then I could do... something... anything.

Thanks. You are more courageous than me. If you find them, please, please don't kill them! I'm sure that there is some sort of cure. Alhelor says that it is permanent, but I still have hope. Perhaps you can talk to Neurik? He's our local priest, you can find him in the mountain side west of the town.
Good, good. I am relieved that he is no longer a werewolf, and alive too. Thank you.
Good to hear that Geth has been cured and is doing fine now. Thank you.
That's great news! I'm glad to hear that he is alive and no longer infected. Thank you.

Yes... the Black Wolf. I've met with my friends, and it turns out that it's actually Alhelor himself! He was disguising himself as a merchant that sells items to ward off the very thing he is. Very cunning...

He is likely hiding out in Wolfhill Manor. An ancient house that has been swallowed up by the Mere of Dead Men. I believe that he is a greater werewolf, which won't be curable by Neurik's silver charms. He... must be destroyed, before anyone else gets afflicted by his cursed disease.

Here, I want you to have this dagger. It's supposed to be very powerful against shapeshifters. Keep it as a reward for saving my friends, and as a weapon against the Black Wolf. The Manor may have all sorts of lycanthropes, so I suggest you bring it there.
Thank you. I know this is a task that must be done for the good of Highcliff, and I wish you luck. You are certainly the bravest of us all.
Hello there. Is there something the matter? Did you have something to ask of me?
I wish you luck in defeating the Black Wolf.
He is likely hiding out in his manor, which is situated below Wolfhill Way. It's southeast of Highcliff, below Crossroad Keep.

Truly? Then we can finally be at rest. Thank you for ending the reign of terror put on this town. Here, I'd like you to have this as a reward. It's one of the items Alhelor wanted me to sell, obviously there's no use in that anymore.
Is there something troubling you?
Can you tell me where your friends are again?
I've returned from Neurik. He has provided me with silver charms that may cure the disease.
I'd like to ask you some questions.
What's going on in Highcliff?

Comment.value: ONLY IF PC has spoken with Alhelor already.

Cha 11+, Int 9+
(charisma generally allows more dialogue options to be
made available to the player, as you can generally chat
with people for longer periods.  Note that this is seperate
from plot givers, who give players required info, not optional
info.]

Int 9+

** one assumes that the 'main plot' is the overarching story
for your module that the player already knows something about...
or, at least, some publicly-known event that the player is aware of.

These dialogues also assume that there are at least three major elements
to the main plot that can be asked about.  If there aren't, extras can be deleted.
As well, if the player doesn't start off knowing about the 'main plot', a script could
easily be added to the question that links into these (the 'I'm curious about some recent
events...') that only makes the option available once the player has been told
about the plot. **

Int 9+, Wis 14+
This is an 'insight'...there are some paths in the dialogue
where a wise character will get the option to ask the right
question and therefore receive more information
